In order to fulfil our mission, we conceived a hybrid international legal group named The Guernica Group. The GCIJ is the non-profit arm inside a legal group that includes affiliated entities in the United Kingdom, Spain and the United States of America, namely Guernica 37 International Justice Chambers (Guernica37) and G37 Despacho Internacional (G37). &#xd;
&#xd;
Globally, these three organisations—Guernica37 in London, G37 in Madrid, and GCIJ in London and California—also secure a specialized capability in civil law and common law legal systems as well as in international justice mechanisms, converging in a shared ultimate goal: to ensure that victims and their communities have the highly technical, specialised and thoughtful representation they deserve. Furthermore, this international structure provides the Group with the practical flexibility to engage in diverse and multi-faceted projects—adapting to the needs and characteristics of the victims and organisations we work with—and builds a unique platform to facilitate collaboration between practitioners from different parts of the globe.&#xd;
&#xd;
At present, The Guernica Group is developing projects in different regions of the world, pursuing accountability to punish perpetrators of international crimes committed in Colombia, Syria, Bangladesh, Gambia, Sri Lanka, El Salvador, Venezuela, Nigeria, Libya and Nicaragua.&#xd;
&#xd;
